The '''Committee on Justice''' ({{lang-nl|Commissie voor de Justitie}}, {{lang-fr|Commission de la Justice}}) is a [[standing committee]] of the [[Belgian Chamber of Representatives]]. It is responsible for all matters related to the administration of [[justice]]. The committee consists of 17 members and is currently chaired by [[Claude Eerdekens]] ([[Socialist Party (francophone Belgium)|PS]]). The seats on the committee are divided among [[Christian Democratic and Flemish|CD&V]]/[[New-Flemish Alliance|N-VA]] (4 seats), [[Reformist Movement|MR]] (3 seats), [[Socialist Party (francophone Belgium)|PS]] (2 seats), [[Open Vlaamse Liberalen en Democraten|Open Flemish Liberals and Democrats]] (2 seats), [[Vlaams Belang]] (2 seats), [[Socialist Party – Different|SP.A]]-[[Spirit (Belgium)|Spirit]] (2 seats), [[Ecolo]]-[[Green!|Groen!]] (1 seat) and [[Humanist Democratic Centre|CDH]] (1 seat).

