{{Politics of Denmark}}
A [[non-binding referendum|non-binding]] '''referendum on the Single European Act''' was held in [[Denmark]] on 27 February 1986.<ref name=DN>[[Dieter Nohlen]] & Philip Stöver (2010) ''Elections in Europe: A data handbook'', p525 {{ISBN|978-3-8329-5609-7}}</ref> It was approved by 56.2% of voters,<ref name="euoplysningen">[http://www.eu-oplysningen.dk/dkeu/dk/afstemninger/afstemning/1986/ Folkeafstemning om EF-pakken] EU Oplysningen {{da icon}}</ref> with a voter participation of 75.4%.<ref>Nohlen & Stöver, p534</ref>
The referendum was held by the government of the [[Prime Minister of Denmark]], [[Poul Schlüter]]. The government was in favour of Denmark ratifying the [[Single European Act]], but a majority in [[Folketinget|parliament]] was against it.<ref name="euoplysningen"/> The referendum was the last Europe-related referendum in which parties such as the [[Social Democrats (Denmark)|Social Democrats]] and the [[Social Liberal Party (Denmark)|Social Liberal Party]] recommended against ratification.
