{{Infobox National flag | Name = Belgrade | Type = City | Image = Flag of Belgrade.svg | Image_size = 200px | Proportion = | Adoption = 1931 | Design = | Designer = [[Đorđe Andrejević-Kun]] }}
The '''flag of [[Belgrade]]''' is composed of three [[Serbia]]n national [[colour]]s: red, blue and white. The blue symbolises [[hope]] and faith in better future. The red of the ground is a symbol of the suffering of Serbian people in a struggle for freedom. Two horizontal white lines represent the Sava and Danube rivers, which are symbols of the strength of Belgrade. They are white according to [[heraldry]] rules. "Beograd" is Serbian name for "white city," so there are white walls and towers. The walls represent a merchant city; the towers and open gate represent an open market. The ship, a [[Ancient Rome|Roman]] [[trireme]], is a symbol of the antiquity of the city.
The flag is a banner of the [[Coat of arms of Belgrade|arms of Belgrade]].
