{{Infobox building | name = Presidential Palace of Cape Verde | native_name = Palácio da Presidência da República | native_name_lang = pt | image = Praia-Palácio_Presidencial_(1).jpg | image_size = | image_alt = | image_caption = | map_type = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of the Presidential Palace in Cape Verde | map_size = | map_dot_label = Presidential Palace of Cape Verde | relief = | former_names = Palácio do Governo de Cabo Verde | alternate_names = | etymology = | status = | building_type = | architectural_style = [[Neoclassical architecture|Neoclassical]] | classification = | location = | address = [[Rua Serpa Pinto]] | location_city = [[Praia]] | location_country = [[Cape Verde]] | coordinates = {{Coord|14.9164|-23.5092|display=inline,title}} | altitude = | current_tenants = | namesake = | groundbreaking_date = | start_date = | stop_date = | completion_date = ca. 1894 | opened_date = | inauguration_date = | renovation_date = 2015 | cost = | floor_count = 2 }} The '''Palácio da Presidência da República''' ([[Portuguese language|Portuguese]] for "Palace of the Presidency of the Republic") is a public building in the city centre of [[Praia]], the capital of [[Cape Verde]]. It is situated on [[Rua Serpa Pinto]], at the south end of [[Plateau (Praia)|Plateau]], the historic district of Praia. It was constructed around 1894 in [[neoclassical architecture|neoclassical style]] as a residence of the [[Portugal|Portuguese]] [[List of colonial governors of Cape Verde|governor of Cape Verde]]. After Cape Verde gained independence in 1975, it became the [[List of Presidents of Cape Verde|presidential]] palace.<ref name=gomes>[http://hdl.handle.net/11328/594 Valor simbólico do centro histórico da Praia], Lourenço Conceição Gomes, Universidade Portucalense, 2008, p. 167-192</ref>
