{{Infobox book | <!-- See [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Novels]] or [[Wikipedia:WikiProject Books]] --> | name = The Book of Proper Names | title_orig = Robert des noms propres | translator = Shaun Whiteside | image = The Book of Proper Names.jpg| author = [[Amélie Nothomb]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = Belgium | language = [[French language|French]] | genre = [[Novel]] | publisher = | release_date = 2002 | english_release_date = | media_type = | pages = 170 | isbn = 2-226-13389-5 | preceded_by = [[The Enemy's Cosmetique]] | followed_by = [[Antichrista]] }}
'''''The Book of Proper Names'''''<ref>{{Cite book|title = The Book of Proper Names: A Novel|url = https://www.amazon.com/Book-Proper-Names-Novel-ebook/dp/B00YM40MV2/ref=sr_1_1?ie=UTF8&qid=1449760321&sr=8-1&keywords=the+book+of+proper+names|publisher = St. Martin's Press|date = 2015-07-21|first = Amelie|last = Nothomb}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = The Book of Proper Names|url = https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/1003801.The_Book_of_Proper_Names|website = Goodreads|accessdate = 2015-12-10}}</ref> ({{lang-fr|'''Robert des noms propres'''}}) is a Belgian novel by [[Amélie Nothomb]].<ref>{{Cite web|title = Amélie Nothomb|url = https://www.goodreads.com/author/show/40416.Am_lie_Nothomb|website = Goodreads|accessdate = 2015-12-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Amazon.com: Amélie Nothomb: Books, Biography, Blog, Audiobooks, Kindle|url = https://www.amazon.com/Am%25C3%25A9lie-Nothomb/e/B00457MXBS|website = www.amazon.com|accessdate = 2015-12-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = A writer's life: Amélie Nothomb|url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/3654008/A-writers-life-Amelie-Nothomb.html|website = Telegraph.co.uk|accessdate = 2015-12-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Amélie Nothomb {{!}} BÉNIS SOIENT CEUX QUI INSPIRENT L'AMOUR.|url = http://www.amelie-nothomb.com/|website = www.amelie-nothomb.com|accessdate = 2015-12-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Amélie Nothomb {{!}} The Institute of Modern Languages Research|url = http://modernlanguages.sas.ac.uk/centre-study-contemporary-womens-writing/languages/french/am%25C3%25A9lie-nothomb|website = modernlanguages.sas.ac.uk|accessdate = 2015-12-10}}</ref> It was first published in 2002. It is a romanticized account of the life of the singer [[Robert (singer)|RoBERT]],<ref>{{Cite web|title = RoBERT - Nouvel album le 24 mars avec Plastic Art Noise|url = http://robertlesite.net/|website = robertlesite.net|accessdate = 2015-12-10}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = Myriam Roulet / France Inter|url = http://www.franceinter.fr/personne-robert-0|website = France Inter|accessdate = 2015-12-11}}</ref> whom Nothomb became acquainted with as an avid admirer of her songs.<ref>{{Citation|url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0fWlX90qvBQ|website= youtube|title= "Chanteuse RoBERT parle du roman d'Amélie Nothomb" |accessdate = 2015-12-10}}</ref> ==Plot== In a vaguely surreal story, an extraordinary little girl is born from strange circumstances - her mother murdered her father, gave birth in prison, and then hanged herself. Plectrude, as the girl is unfortunately named by her mother, is adopted by her aunt and lives a fairy-like existence until she enrolls into the Paris Opera Ballet School, a rigorous institution portrayed as a "scalpel to slice away the last flesh of childhood."<ref>{{Cite web|title = Review: The Book of Proper Names by Am&#233;lie Nothomb|url = https://www.theguardian.com/books/2004/may/29/featuresreviews.guardianreview18|website = the Guardian|accessdate = 2015-12-10|first = Kate|last = Figes}}</ref><ref>[https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/books/3617057/Murdered-by-her-heroine.html Telegraph.co.uk, Jasper Rees, "Murdered by her heroine", 15 May 2004]</ref><ref>[http://www.scotsman.com/lifestyle/culture/books/a-twisted-ballerina-s-dance-macabre-1-1393994 The Scotsman, "A twisted ballerina's dance macabre" 09, May 2004]</ref>
